Senator Yakubu Lado Danmarke has emerged the winner of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) gubernatorial election held on Thursday. Announcing the result, the Electoral Committee chairman, Mr Chika Nwozuzu, declared Senator Danmarke winner with 740 votes to beat his distant rival, Hon. Salisu Yusuf Majigiri, who polled 257 votes, Architect Ahmed Yar’Adua, who scored 53 votes, and Hon. Shehu Inuwa Imam, who scored 44 votes. Out of total of 1,117 delegates drawn across the 34 local government areas of the State, 1,108 delegates were accredited, 10 invalid votes were recorded while four delegates abstained from voting after accreditation. Danmarke, a businessman, was born in 1961. He became a Member of the House of Representatives from 2003–2007 and was elected a Senator in April 2007 for Katsina South senatorial district of Katsina State on the platform of the PDP.